text.tspan: Beyond its nutritional value, food plays a
significant cultural and social role, influencing
traditions, lifestyles, and economies worldwide.
Food
Industrial refers to the sector of an economy
characterized by the large-scale production of
goods and services using advanced machinery
and technology.
Industrial
A household is a fundamental social unit typically
consisting of individuals who live together in a shared
dwelling and manage their domestic life collectively.
Household
Medical refers to the science and practice of
diagnosing, treating, and preventing diseases and
injuries to improve and maintain human health.
Medical
As consumer awareness about health and
environmental impacts rises, the personal care
sector continues to evolve, promoting holistic and
eco-friendly approaches to self-care.
Personal Care
Agriculture, the cornerstone of human civilization,
involves the cultivation of soil, the growing of crops,
and the raising of animals for food, fiber, and other
essential products.
Agriculture
